And all the cities that he took!—without crossing the ford of the river Halys, and without stirring forth from his own hearth: such, for instance, as the Acheloian cities
of the Strymonic gulf, established near the Thracian dwellings;
And, outside the estuary, the cities on the mainland fortified round about by towers owned him as king, and the cities, too, which are proud [to be] round about the strait of Helle; and embayed Propontis, and the [Thracian] outlet of Pontus;
